text: Alfred Meyer-Waldeck (27 November 1864 – 25 August 1928) was a vice admiral in the Imperial German Navy from 1909 to 1914. He was most notable as the lead naval commander in the Siege of Tsingtao during World War I and the final governor of the Kiautschou Bay concession from 1911 to 1914. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1864 births Category:1928 deaths Category:German military personnel of World War I Category:Imperial German Navy admirals of World War I
